1
00:00:05,606 --> 00:00:11,011
Team: ♪ We'll chase the rabbit
into the hills ♪

2
00:00:11,077 --> 00:00:13,113
‐ [laughing]
‐ Does rabbit even taste good?

3
00:00:13,179 --> 00:00:16,282
‐ You never had it?
Rabbit stew's the best.

4
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:18,251
After we catch her,
we should make some.

5
00:00:18,318 --> 00:00:19,886
‐ Ecch. You want to eat her?

6
00:00:19,953 --> 00:00:21,154
Boss: That was a metaphor,

7
00:00:21,221 --> 00:00:23,089
'cause she looks
like a rabbit. Dork!

8
00:00:23,156 --> 00:00:24,457
‐ [team laughing]
‐ Oh, I get it.

9
00:00:24,525 --> 00:00:27,060
Boss: Come on, ladies!
Let's go hunting!

10
00:00:27,127 --> 00:00:28,962
Team: Yeah!

11
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:32,633
M: [crying] Please!
I don't wanna die!

12
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:37,738
Don't shoot!
Don't shoot me, please!

13
00:00:37,804 --> 00:00:40,306
Oh, God, I don't wanna die!

14
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:42,342
Please, no, don't shoot!

15
00:00:42,408 --> 00:00:44,778
‐ Tell me why
you tried to kill me, then.

16
00:00:44,845 --> 00:00:48,214
If you don't, I'm gonna put
a bullet between your eyes.

17
00:00:48,281 --> 00:00:51,017
‐ No, don't. I'll die.

18
00:00:51,084 --> 00:00:52,586
‐ Yeah, that's the idea.

19
00:00:53,486 --> 00:00:56,289
‐ No, I mean I'll die.

20
00:00:56,356 --> 00:00:58,158
‐ Quit jerkin' me around!

21
00:00:58,224 --> 00:01:01,194
Wait. Am I talking
to the same player here?

22
00:01:01,261 --> 00:01:03,564
‐ I didn't switch.
It's still me,

23
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:07,033
and if you shoot me,
I'm going to die.

24
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,069
I don't wanna die!

25
00:01:09,135 --> 00:01:11,237
‐ So what?
It's just in the game.

26
00:01:11,304 --> 00:01:12,706
‐ No, not in the game!

27
00:01:12,773 --> 00:01:14,975
‐ What are you talking about?

28
00:01:15,041 --> 00:01:17,310
‐ If I die in Squad Jam,

29
00:01:17,377 --> 00:01:20,614
the real me in the real world
is gonna die, too.

30
00:01:20,681 --> 00:01:23,517
‐ Oh, come on.
This isn't "Sword Art Online."

31
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:25,786
[gasps] Wait.

32
00:01:25,852 --> 00:01:28,722
Does this have something
to do with that letter?

33
00:01:28,789 --> 00:01:30,691
‐ [crying]

34
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:33,426
[bird shrieks]

35
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:35,762
‐ No tricks, or I'll shoot.

36
00:01:35,829 --> 00:01:37,163
‐ I know.

37
00:01:38,164 --> 00:01:39,399
‐ "Yoo‐hoo, M.

38
00:01:39,465 --> 00:01:40,834
Hope you're fighting hard.

39
00:01:40,901 --> 00:01:44,170
You better be reading this
an hour in like I told you.

40
00:01:44,237 --> 00:01:46,640
I'll kill you
if you tear it up.

41
00:01:46,707 --> 00:01:49,275
[both voices] Remember,
you're playing for me today,

42
00:01:49,342 --> 00:01:50,644
so have fun out there."

43
00:01:50,711 --> 00:01:52,112
Pito: <i>Don't forget it's a game,</i>

44
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:54,447
<i>and games are</i>
<i>all about having fun.</i>

45
00:01:54,515 --> 00:01:56,650
<i>That said,</i>
<i>if you die like some loser</i>

46
00:01:56,717 --> 00:01:59,085
<i>before the first hour,</i>
<i>I'm gonna slaughter you.</i>

47
00:01:59,152 --> 00:02:00,954
<i>But if you guys manage</i>
<i>to survive the hour,</i>

48
00:02:01,021 --> 00:02:03,624
<i>I'll be impressed.</i>
<i>I'll pat you on the head</i>

49
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:05,659
<i>and tell you</i>
<i>how awesome you are.</i>

50
00:02:05,726 --> 00:02:08,028
<i>If you die after that, too bad.</i>
<i>I'll still kill you.</i>

51
00:02:08,094 --> 00:02:09,596
<i>And forget suicide.</i>

52
00:02:09,663 --> 00:02:12,065
<i>Whatever happens,</i>
<i>you have to survive.</i>

53
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:16,036
<i>A battle's no fun without</i>
<i>real life‐or‐death stakes,</i>

54
00:02:16,102 --> 00:02:17,337
<i>no tension.</i>

55
00:02:17,403 --> 00:02:19,606
<i>Now get out there,</i>
<i>and have a blast.</i>

56
00:02:19,673 --> 00:02:21,742
<i>Savor life. Later.</i>

57
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:25,478
‐ Uh, this sounds like
something Pito'd write.

58
00:02:25,546 --> 00:02:26,647
‐ Uh‐huh.

59
00:02:27,548 --> 00:02:28,782
‐ Yeah, but it's not like

60
00:02:28,849 --> 00:02:30,416
she's serious about it.

61
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:33,119
I mean, she can't
be serious, can she?

62
00:02:33,186 --> 00:02:34,287
‐ [gasps]
‐ Huh?

63
00:02:34,354 --> 00:02:35,656
‐ [crazed laugh]

64
00:02:35,722 --> 00:02:38,224
You have no idea
what's going on here!

65
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:41,795
You don't know how crazy
Pitohui really is!

66
00:02:41,862 --> 00:02:43,797
["Ryusei" by Eir Aoi playing]

67
00:02:56,109 --> 00:02:58,244
‐ [singing in Japanese]

68
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:31,311
<i>♪ ...safety ♪</i>

69
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,313
[singing in Japanese]

70
00:03:59,973 --> 00:04:02,442
<i>♪ The darkest night ♪</i>

71
00:04:02,509 --> 00:04:04,645
[singing in Japanese]

72
00:04:06,547 --> 00:04:10,717
<i>♪ The darkest night ♪</i>

73
00:04:14,487 --> 00:04:17,490
M: If Pitohui says
she'll kill you, she means it.

74
00:04:17,558 --> 00:04:19,292
She'll really kill you.

75
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:22,195
"In the game"?
[laughs] Yeah, right.

76
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,830
If I don't do what she says,

77
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:26,432
I know for a fact
she'll murder me.

78
00:04:26,499 --> 00:04:29,469
And she knows I know
she's insane enough to do it,

79
00:04:29,536 --> 00:04:31,471
and that's why
she wrote that letter!

80
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:34,608
She says have fun, but then
says all that other stuff!

81
00:04:34,675 --> 00:04:36,510
Does that sound normal to you?!

82
00:04:36,577 --> 00:04:38,612
She wants
another goddamn death game!

83
00:04:38,679 --> 00:04:40,213
She's still obsessed with it!

84
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,982
Don't you get it?!

85
00:04:42,048 --> 00:04:43,416
[laughs]

86
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:45,485
She's out of her mind!

87
00:04:45,552 --> 00:04:48,088
‐ [sobbing]
‐ Okay, just so we're clear,

88
00:04:48,154 --> 00:04:50,190
you're saying if you die in SJ,

89
00:04:50,256 --> 00:04:52,593
the real Pito
will kill the real you.

90
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:55,796
‐ Y‐Yeah!
Haven't you been listening?!

91
00:04:55,862 --> 00:04:58,665
‐ [sighs]

92
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,835
‐ Thank you for not shooting me.

93
00:05:01,902 --> 00:05:05,672
‐ You still haven't told me
why you tried to kill me.

94
00:05:05,739 --> 00:05:09,042
‐ If you died,
then I'd be team leader.

95
00:05:09,109 --> 00:05:10,877
‐ Yeah, and then what?

96
00:05:10,944 --> 00:05:12,546
‐ I'd resign.

97
00:05:12,613 --> 00:05:15,616
‐ Hmph.
You underestimated my agility.

98
00:05:15,682 --> 00:05:19,385
‐ You're right. I should have
used a grenade instead.

99
00:05:19,452 --> 00:05:21,154
‐ [stammers]

100
00:05:21,221 --> 00:05:23,690
Well, you didn't, so yay me.

101
00:05:23,757 --> 00:05:25,325
1515.

102
00:05:25,391 --> 00:05:27,694
[thinking]
<i>The scan finished a while ago.</i>

103
00:05:27,761 --> 00:05:30,263
<i>The other team could be close.</i>

104
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:31,331
Oh, whatever.

105
00:05:31,397 --> 00:05:33,567
M, you're on your own.

106
00:05:33,634 --> 00:05:35,669
I'm a one‐woman
strike force now.

107
00:05:35,736 --> 00:05:37,604
Go find yourself
a place to hide.

108
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:41,007
If I get killed,
you can surrender. I don't care.

109
00:05:41,074 --> 00:05:43,777
Thanks for everything. See ya!

110
00:05:44,845 --> 00:05:46,780
‐ [stammering]

111
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:50,216
<i>‐ What do I do?</i>

112
00:05:50,283 --> 00:05:52,753
<i>What skill can I use</i>
<i>to win this?</i>

113
00:05:52,819 --> 00:05:56,657
<i>Of course, the best one I have.</i>

114
00:05:56,723 --> 00:05:59,726
<i>Yeah! I'll run like crazy.</i>

115
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:04,598
M: It's not my fault.
I know I'm right.

116
00:06:04,665 --> 00:06:07,934
They can call me a coward,
but they don't know her.

117
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:10,136
They don't know
how scary she is.

118
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:13,006
It's totally natural
to be scared of dying.

119
00:06:13,073 --> 00:06:15,676
They can't blame me
for wanting to live.

120
00:06:15,742 --> 00:06:17,611
LLENN: [radio]
<i>Time to kick some ass!</i>

121
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:20,614
[thinking]
<i>It's the last battle,</i>

122
00:06:20,681 --> 00:06:22,482
<i>and I'm gonna fight to the end!</i>

123
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:25,418
<i>Or as far as I can get.</i>

124
00:06:32,425 --> 00:06:34,060
‐ I got you now!

125
00:06:34,127 --> 00:06:35,962
[music playing]

126
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:42,536
‐ [thinking] <i>Dang it.</i>

127
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:51,411
‐ [grunts]

128
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:53,847
[gasps]

129
00:07:01,354 --> 00:07:03,189
[groans]

130
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,591
‐ [gasps]

131
00:07:15,902 --> 00:07:18,238
‐ Enemy sighted!
She's carrying a P90.

132
00:07:18,304 --> 00:07:20,340
She's fast as hell!

133
00:07:20,406 --> 00:07:21,775
[gasps]

134
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:32,152
‐ That's one!

135
00:07:32,218 --> 00:07:33,787
[gasps]

136
00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:37,157
[yelps]

137
00:07:37,223 --> 00:07:38,158
[shrieks]

138
00:07:40,426 --> 00:07:42,162
‐ You're dead!

139
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:44,931
[grunting]

140
00:07:49,369 --> 00:07:51,271
Anna: Bye‐bye.

141
00:07:51,337 --> 00:07:52,472
Damn it!

142
00:07:52,539 --> 00:07:54,340
[firing]

143
00:07:54,407 --> 00:07:56,710
‐ [shrieks]

144
00:07:56,777 --> 00:08:00,046
How many times
do I have to do this?!

145
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:07,087
[footsteps approaching]

146
00:08:10,223 --> 00:08:12,626
‐ I swear
I'll make her pay for this.

147
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:17,631
I want you or Sophie
to have this.

148
00:08:17,698 --> 00:08:20,967
If you get the chance to,
wound her.

149
00:08:22,035 --> 00:08:24,505
‐ Roger that. Eh?

150
00:08:26,139 --> 00:08:29,543
‐ I get the kill shot
for this one.

151
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:30,877
[chuckles]

152
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,648
[bird warbling]

153
00:08:34,715 --> 00:08:36,683
‐ HP's at 70.

154
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,719
Only six mags left.

155
00:08:41,655 --> 00:08:44,558
What can I do
with two grenades...

156
00:08:45,425 --> 00:08:46,593
and a knife?

157
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,928
A suicide run?

158
00:08:47,994 --> 00:08:50,163
‐ [automatic gunfire]
‐ [yelps]

159
00:08:51,464 --> 00:08:54,535
They're 200 meters away,
at least.

160
00:08:54,601 --> 00:08:57,303
[automatic gunfire]

161
00:08:57,370 --> 00:09:00,306
Pito: <i>LLENN, if your back's</i>
<i>against the wall,</i>

162
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:03,844
<i>whatever you do,</i>
<i>don't start shooting wildly.</i>

163
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:06,680
<i>It's like a drug that helps you</i>
<i>forget you're afraid,</i>

164
00:09:06,747 --> 00:09:08,782
<i>but only as long</i>
<i>as you're firing.</i>

165
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:10,517
<i>All it does is waste ammo</i>

166
00:09:10,584 --> 00:09:12,586
<i>and give away</i>
<i>your location to the enemy,</i>

167
00:09:12,653 --> 00:09:15,321
<i>and worse,</i>
<i>it tells them you're scared.</i>

168
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:17,624
<i>It's a bad decision all around.</i>

169
00:09:17,691 --> 00:09:19,826
‐ Maybe I can still win.

170
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:30,036
<i>Yeah. I'll kill them all</i>
<i>and win this.</i>

171
00:09:30,103 --> 00:09:31,805
<i>I can't wait to see the look</i>

172
00:09:31,872 --> 00:09:33,907
<i>on M and Pito's faces</i>
<i>when I do.</i>

173
00:09:33,974 --> 00:09:34,908
[gasps]

174
00:09:47,821 --> 00:09:50,724
‐ Damn.
You're one lucky bastard.

175
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,626
My shot winged her, is all.

176
00:09:52,693 --> 00:09:54,628
She's on the run, heading south.

177
00:09:54,695 --> 00:09:57,063
Get on her tail, and stay sharp.

178
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:58,264
Team: [radio]
<i>Roger that!</i>

179
00:10:00,534 --> 00:10:02,235
‐ Next time, shrimp.

180
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,672
‐ [panting]

181
00:10:05,739 --> 00:10:07,574
Darn sniper.

182
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:10,310
They got so close so fast.

183
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:13,514
[gasps] They set a trap.

184
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:16,750
That's what all the shooting
was for, to draw me out.

185
00:10:16,817 --> 00:10:19,185
They survived all this time.
I should have known

186
00:10:19,252 --> 00:10:22,355
they wouldn't give away
their position that easy.

187
00:10:22,422 --> 00:10:23,890
[groans]

188
00:10:26,593 --> 00:10:27,694
That's okay.

189
00:10:27,761 --> 00:10:29,763
I'm still alive.

190
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:31,632
I‐I can move.

191
00:10:31,698 --> 00:10:33,233
I'm still lucky.

192
00:10:34,334 --> 00:10:36,703
‐ Found her! Below the sun!

193
00:10:37,738 --> 00:10:39,072
Hundred meters!

194
00:10:44,277 --> 00:10:45,679
‐ She behind that rock?

195
00:10:45,746 --> 00:10:46,713
‐ <i>Da!</i>

196
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:48,815
‐ Give me your shoulder.

197
00:10:50,684 --> 00:10:53,253
Time to die, rabbit!

198
00:10:56,590 --> 00:10:58,892
‐ [squealing]

199
00:10:58,959 --> 00:11:01,895
<i>Oh, no. This is bad.</i>
<i>I'm a goner for sure.</i>

200
00:11:01,962 --> 00:11:03,897
<i>If I try to run, I'll get shot.</i>

201
00:11:03,964 --> 00:11:07,133
<i>If I stay, they'll toss</i>
<i>a grenade and blow me up.</i>

202
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,268
[gasps]

203
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,236
[gunfire continues]

204
00:11:10,303 --> 00:11:11,805
<i>Can it work?</i>

205
00:11:11,872 --> 00:11:14,207
<i>Only one way to find out.</i>

206
00:11:15,509 --> 00:11:16,777
<i>One...</i>

207
00:11:18,645 --> 00:11:19,980
<i>two...</i>

208
00:11:21,515 --> 00:11:23,049
<i>three.</i>

209
00:11:29,255 --> 00:11:32,325
‐ Crap.
That explosion's for cover.

210
00:11:34,661 --> 00:11:38,198
She's going west, heading
for those rock formations.

211
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:39,332
Team: <i>Roger that!</i>

212
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:42,068
‐ She's good, very good.

213
00:11:42,135 --> 00:11:45,238
‐ Yeah, she is. We fought
some tough ones up to now,

214
00:11:45,305 --> 00:11:47,140
but this one's gotta be
the toughest yet.

215
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:51,444
‐ It worked. It worked.
It worked! It worked!

216
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:53,847
Whoo‐hoo!

217
00:11:53,914 --> 00:11:56,249
I'll just keep running
and running and running

218
00:11:56,316 --> 00:11:58,018
and running...

219
00:12:00,687 --> 00:12:03,289
<i>And then what?</i>

220
00:12:03,356 --> 00:12:04,925
<i>I can't run forever.</i>

221
00:12:07,027 --> 00:12:10,964
<i>What did I do that helped me</i>
<i>survive this long?</i>

222
00:12:11,031 --> 00:12:13,099
<i>How did I beat anyone?</i>

223
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:15,401
<i>I was up close.</i>

224
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:19,606
<i>Whenever I killed an enemy,</i>
<i>I was always up close.</i>

225
00:12:19,673 --> 00:12:23,544
That's it. I shouldn't run.

226
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:24,978
‐ Attagirl, LLENN!

227
00:12:25,045 --> 00:12:27,247
‐ You finally figured it out!
‐ [gasps]

228
00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:29,983
‐ Stop running away
from the enemy.

229
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:32,686
Run straight at them instead!

230
00:12:32,753 --> 00:12:33,854
‐ What the heck?!

231
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,756
‐ Use your speed and agility,

232
00:12:35,822 --> 00:12:38,391
and fight your way,
the best way.

233
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:40,861
‐ It's talking.

234
00:12:41,962 --> 00:12:44,264
‐ Don't worry. I got your back.

235
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,732
‐ This isn't happening!
This isn't happening!

236
00:12:45,799 --> 00:12:47,200
‐ This isn't happening!
‐ Live or die...

237
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,669
‐ This isn't happening!
‐ we'll fight together!

238
00:12:48,735 --> 00:12:52,405
‐ This can't be happening!

239
00:12:54,708 --> 00:12:57,443
[walking footsteps]

240
00:12:57,511 --> 00:12:59,445
‐ [thinking] <i>Where is she?</i>

241
00:12:59,513 --> 00:13:01,381
<i>When I find her, I am gonna‐‐</i>

242
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:02,382
Woman: Boss!

243
00:13:03,617 --> 00:13:05,218
‐ Looking for me?

244
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:07,353
‐ Yeah.

245
00:13:12,392 --> 00:13:14,460
‐ [giggles]

246
00:13:15,562 --> 00:13:16,863
My turn.

247
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:29,142
‐ Damn it!
