266
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:53,927
‐ [gags]

267
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:56,663
[yells]

268
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,502
‐ It's over!

269
00:15:05,138 --> 00:15:07,941
Damn it. Why won't you die?!

270
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:12,012
‐ Ow, that smarts.

271
00:15:12,078 --> 00:15:13,747
‐ Are you immortal or something?

272
00:15:13,814 --> 00:15:15,716
‐ Uh...

273
00:15:15,782 --> 00:15:17,984
‐ Wha?! "Immortal object"?

274
00:15:18,051 --> 00:15:19,553
Her scan terminal!

275
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:21,054
All right.

276
00:15:23,323 --> 00:15:24,625
[clicking]

277
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:26,059
Damn it.

278
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:28,595
‐ [grunts]
‐ [grunts]

279
00:15:28,662 --> 00:15:29,730
‐ [yells]

280
00:15:29,796 --> 00:15:31,197
‐ [yelps]

281
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,502
[yells]

282
00:15:40,974 --> 00:15:43,143
‐ You're hit. Doesn't that hurt?

283
00:15:43,209 --> 00:15:45,812
‐ I didn't notice
in all the excitement.

284
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:47,280
‐ Trust me. It looks painful!

285
00:15:47,347 --> 00:15:50,551
‐ If it makes you feel better,
my grip's weak.

286
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:51,852
‐ You could have fooled me.

287
00:15:51,918 --> 00:15:54,220
‐ So, munchkin,
what's your handle?

288
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:56,723
‐ It's LLENN. And what's yours?

289
00:15:56,790 --> 00:16:01,127
‐ It's Eva, but everyone
just calls me Boss.

290
00:16:01,194 --> 00:16:02,763
You're out of ammo.

291
00:16:02,829 --> 00:16:04,497
‐ That makes two of us.

292
00:16:04,565 --> 00:16:05,699
‐ Boss!
‐ [gasps]

293
00:16:06,767 --> 00:16:07,701
Boss: Sophie!

294
00:16:07,768 --> 00:16:09,736
Hurry! Shoot us both!

295
00:16:09,803 --> 00:16:10,737
Sophie: No!

296
00:16:10,804 --> 00:16:11,905
Boss: Shoot, damn it!

297
00:16:11,972 --> 00:16:13,439
‐ [gasps]

298
00:16:13,507 --> 00:16:14,440
[groans]

299
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,982
‐ Hey, Boss, heads up!

300
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:24,084
[gags]

301
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:37,731
‐ [gasps]

302
00:16:39,132 --> 00:16:41,001
Nice catch.

303
00:16:46,072 --> 00:16:48,542
[no audible dialogue]

304
00:16:49,475 --> 00:16:51,011
P‐chan: Don't you worry, LLENN.

305
00:16:51,077 --> 00:16:52,513
I'm here to protect you.

306
00:16:52,579 --> 00:16:53,514
‐ [gasps]

307
00:17:03,223 --> 00:17:05,626
‐ Yeah, you like that?!

308
00:17:05,692 --> 00:17:06,893
LLENN: How dare you?

309
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,094
‐ Eh?

310
00:17:10,531 --> 00:17:12,599
‐ You rotten...

311
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:17,871
You killed my precious P‐chan!

312
00:17:17,938 --> 00:17:19,973
‐ Let's try this again.

313
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,341
["Independence"
by Elza Kanzaki playing]

314
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:22,943
‐ [singing in Japanese]

315
00:17:23,009 --> 00:17:24,477
‐ You can't get away.

316
00:17:24,545 --> 00:17:25,278
[gags]

317
00:17:25,345 --> 00:17:26,847
[yelps] You cut me!

318
00:17:26,913 --> 00:17:28,214
‐ [yells]

319
00:17:30,551 --> 00:17:31,685
‐ [groans]

320
00:17:31,752 --> 00:17:32,686
‐ <i>♪ Blind faith ♪</i>

321
00:17:32,753 --> 00:17:34,621
[singing in Japanese]

322
00:17:35,689 --> 00:17:36,657
[grunts]

323
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:38,959
<i>‐ ♪ Cogito ergo sum ♪</i>

324
00:17:39,025 --> 00:17:41,161
[singing in Japanese]

325
00:17:42,362 --> 00:17:44,397
‐ [thinking] <i>I win.</i>

326
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:47,100
[gasps] <i>No.</i>

327
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:49,503
<i>She let go of it.</i>

328
00:17:49,570 --> 00:17:50,804
[laughs]

329
00:17:57,511 --> 00:17:58,812
‐ <i>♪ Don't discard ♪</i>

330
00:17:58,879 --> 00:18:00,747
[singing in Japanese]

331
00:18:02,082 --> 00:18:04,217
‐ [gagging]

332
00:18:05,351 --> 00:18:06,987
‐ <i>♪ Independence ♪</i>

333
00:18:07,053 --> 00:18:09,189
[singing in Japanese]

334
00:18:12,993 --> 00:18:14,661
‐ I‐I did it!

335
00:18:14,728 --> 00:18:15,796
M: <i>Duck!</i>

336
00:18:15,862 --> 00:18:17,097
‐ [gasps]

337
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,602
[M whistles]

338
00:18:25,238 --> 00:18:27,140
‐ Da, I see you.

339
00:18:45,626 --> 00:18:46,627
‐ M!

340
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:52,298
Announcer: <i>Congratulations!</i>

341
00:18:52,365 --> 00:18:54,901
<i>The winner is team LM!</i>

342
00:18:54,968 --> 00:18:56,903
[running footsteps]

343
00:18:58,438 --> 00:18:59,205
‐ M!

344
00:18:59,272 --> 00:19:00,440
[gasps] Oh, God!

345
00:19:02,709 --> 00:19:04,177
[screams]

346
00:19:04,244 --> 00:19:06,780
His head's twisted around!

347
00:19:06,847 --> 00:19:08,181
‐ [grunts]

348
00:19:08,248 --> 00:19:10,617
‐ [screams] He's a zombie!

349
00:19:10,684 --> 00:19:12,919
‐ M: You're so loud.
‐ Ohh?

350
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:15,656
Jeez, M. Why did you

351
00:19:15,722 --> 00:19:17,457
have to go
and scare me like that?

352
00:19:17,524 --> 00:19:19,826
‐ Uh, about before, sorry,

353
00:19:19,893 --> 00:19:22,963
but I really,
really didn't wanna die.

354
00:19:23,029 --> 00:19:24,798
[fireworks booming]

355
00:19:24,865 --> 00:19:26,266
‐ [giggles]

356
00:19:27,601 --> 00:19:30,504
Announcer:
<i>That's it, Squad Jammers!</i>

357
00:19:30,571 --> 00:19:33,707
<i>Game over!</i>

358
00:19:35,308 --> 00:19:37,644
<i>And the winner is team LM.</i>

359
00:19:37,711 --> 00:19:41,081
<i>Total time was one hour</i>
<i>and 28 minutes,</i>

360
00:19:41,147 --> 00:19:43,717
<i>and the total shots</i>
<i>fired was...</i>

361
00:19:43,784 --> 00:19:48,622
‐ [crowd cheering]
‐ <i>49,810 shots!</i>

362
00:19:48,689 --> 00:19:52,025
["To see the future"
by Tomori Kusunoki playing]

363
00:19:52,092 --> 00:19:54,227
[singing in Japanese]

364
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:46,279
<i>♪ You say good night ♪</i>

365
00:20:46,346 --> 00:20:48,481
[singing in Japanese]

366
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,502
<i>♪ To see the future ♪</i>

367
00:21:22,816 --> 00:21:26,720
‐ Excuse me. I hate to bother
you like this, but...

368
00:21:26,787 --> 00:21:29,923
a‐are you the same lady
we pass every day?

369
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:31,391
‐ Uh, yeah, I am.

370
00:21:31,457 --> 00:21:32,893
‐ Did you...

371
00:21:32,959 --> 00:21:34,027
cut your hair?

372
00:21:34,094 --> 00:21:36,663
‐ Yeah. I had it done yesterday.

373
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:39,833
‐ They did a great job.
You look good!

374
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,636
‐ Oh! R‐Really?

375
00:21:42,703 --> 00:21:45,939
‐ Yeah! If you're not a model,
you totally should be.

376
00:21:46,006 --> 00:21:48,441
Every time we see you,
we can't stop talking

377
00:21:48,509 --> 00:21:50,777
about how tall
and stylish you are.

378
00:21:50,844 --> 00:21:53,013
I mean, we're all
so short, you know?

379
00:21:53,079 --> 00:21:55,415
I like how you looked before
with long hair,

380
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:57,618
but this looks
even better on you.

381
00:21:57,684 --> 00:22:00,821
‐ Wow. Um, well, thank you.

382
00:22:00,887 --> 00:22:05,191
‐ I wish I were tall,
but I think I stopped growing.

383
00:22:05,258 --> 00:22:07,828
‐ To be honest,
until the other day,

384
00:22:07,894 --> 00:22:11,197
I hated being tall,
and then‐‐I don't know.

385
00:22:11,264 --> 00:22:14,367
It just didn't matter anymore.

386
00:22:14,434 --> 00:22:16,036
Then I got my hair cut.

387
00:22:16,102 --> 00:22:19,272
‐ You got over it
just like that? How'd you do it?

388
00:22:19,339 --> 00:22:21,742
‐ Oh. Well, um...

389
00:22:21,808 --> 00:22:25,946
I was doing something where
I had to risk my life a bunch.

390
00:22:26,012 --> 00:22:29,249
It helped me realize I could
do anything if I didn't give up.

391
00:22:29,315 --> 00:22:31,718
‐ Wow. That's awesome.

392
00:22:32,586 --> 00:22:33,954
‐ You see that, Boss?

393
00:22:34,020 --> 00:22:35,221
Told you she'd be cool.

394
00:22:35,288 --> 00:22:36,557
‐ Uh, Boss?

395
00:22:36,623 --> 00:22:38,692
‐ [laughs]
Yeah, it's a weird nickname.

396
00:22:38,759 --> 00:22:41,828
Anyway, my real name
is Saki Nitobe.

397
00:22:41,895 --> 00:22:43,664
I'm a junior
at the high school here.

398
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:46,032
We're on the rhythmic
gymnastics team,

399
00:22:46,099 --> 00:22:47,634
and I'm the captain.

400
00:22:47,701 --> 00:22:51,171
‐ My name's Karen,
Karen Kohiruimaki,

401
00:22:51,237 --> 00:22:52,438
and I go to the college.

402
00:22:52,506 --> 00:22:54,575
‐ You got the coolest name.

403
00:22:54,641 --> 00:22:56,977
‐ Thanks, Saki.
It's nice to meet you all.

404
00:22:57,043 --> 00:23:00,380
‐ Is it okay if the next time
we see you, we stop and chat?

405
00:23:00,446 --> 00:23:01,347
‐ Sure.

406
00:23:01,414 --> 00:23:03,349
‐ Sweet. We totally will!

407
00:23:03,416 --> 00:23:04,384
Well...

408
00:23:04,450 --> 00:23:05,519
All: See you later.

409
00:23:05,586 --> 00:23:07,120
Karen: See you.

410
00:23:12,492 --> 00:23:13,927
No way.

411
00:23:13,994 --> 00:23:15,796
[laughs]

412
00:23:17,097 --> 00:23:18,599
Saki: Karen?

413
00:23:18,665 --> 00:23:20,066
It's me again.

414
00:23:20,133 --> 00:23:24,104
Before you go, is it okay
if I shake your hand?

415
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:26,540
‐ Um, yeah, okay.

416
00:23:31,044 --> 00:23:32,445
‐ [chuckles]

417
00:23:32,513 --> 00:23:33,714
Congrats on your win,

418
00:23:33,780 --> 00:23:36,049
but next time, it's gonna be us.

419
00:23:36,116 --> 00:23:37,551
Got it, munchkin?

420
00:23:38,451 --> 00:23:40,386
‐ I'm ready anytime you are...

421
00:23:40,453 --> 00:23:41,922
you Amazon.

422
00:23:41,988 --> 00:23:44,791
Both: See ya in "GGO."

